Noor Financial Investment KSCC signed
an agreement with  Kuwait Finance House (KFIN)  to reschedule loans of 44
million dinars ($158 million), according to a statement filed on
the Kuwait Stock Exchange today.  The reorganized amount, to be converted to long-term loans
from short-term loans, accounts for 28 percent of Noorâ€™s total
debt, Noor said in the statement. The Kuwait-based investment
company said it has rescheduled 75 percent of its total debt and
is in talks with other lenders for similar agreements.  To contact the reporter on this story:
